<paragraph id="7921D1F8AEF39723FB818A6C6836DEE0" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="09D605EEF2324EB6CAB7444CEA9AA02E" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
Palaearctic Region: China (Guangdong, Guangxi, Guizhou, Hainan, Hong Kong, Yunnan); Bhutan; India (Sikkim) (
<bibRefCitation id="F734B6D52FD3343E49B5152AC8B5BC15" author="Yiu, V" journalOrPublisher="Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B161" refString="Yiu, V, 2009. Longhorn Beetles of Hong Kong. Insect Fauna of Hong Kong, Fascicle 1. Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" title="Longhorn Beetles of Hong Kong. Insect Fauna of Hong Kong, Fascicle 1." year="2009">Yiu 2009</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="E28443490CE0B7BD0646CC25D540D347" author="Lin, M-Y" journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B89" refString="Lin, M-Y, Yang, X-K, 2019. Catalogue of Chinese Coleoptera, Vol. IX. Chrysomeloidea: Vesperidae, Disteniidae, Cerambycidae. Science Press, Beijing" title="Catalogue of Chinese Coleoptera, Vol. IX. Chrysomeloidea: Vesperidae, Disteniidae, Cerambycidae." year="2019">Lin and Yang 2019</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="58F82EDE07305FE3320A021102E02BFE" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1163/9789004440333" author="Danilevsky, M" journalOrPublisher=") Synonymia Insectorum, oder Versuch einer Synonymie aller bisher bekannten Insekten; nach Fabricii Systema Eleutheratorum etc. geordnet. Erster Band. Eleutherata oder Kaefer. Tom 1. Dritter Theil. Hispa. Molorchus. Upsala: Em. Bruzelius [xi +] 506 pp. Appendix: Descriptiones novarum specierum" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B25" refString="Danilevsky, M, 2020. Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera, Vol 6/1: Chrysomeloidea I (Vesperidae, Disteniidae, Cerambycidae). Brill, Leiden/Boston, [xxii +] 712 pp. https://doi.org/10.1163/9789004440333" title="Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera, Vol 6 / 1: Chrysomeloidea I (Vesperidae, Disteniidae, Cerambycidae). Brill, Leiden / Boston, [xxii +] 712 pp." url="https://doi.org/10.1163/9789004440333" year="2020">Danilevsky 2020</bibRefCitation>
). Oriental Region: Laos; Malaysia (Malacca); Myanmar; Indonesia (Sumatra); Vietnam (
<bibRefCitation id="542E73B03197DA95F1C493D1D81FA6AB" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4345.1.1" author="Kariyanna, B" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="1 - 317" refId="B73" refString="Kariyanna, B, Mohan, M, Gupta, R, Vitali, F, 2017. The checklist of longhorn beetles (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae) from India. Zootaxa 4345 (1): 1 - 317, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4345.1.1" title="The checklist of longhorn beetles (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae) from India." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4345.1.1" volume="4345" year="2017">Kariyanna et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
). Afrotropical Region: Madagascar (
<bibRefCitation id="B5AA00FA4799AA238BA24432C94F4807" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4345.1.1" author="Kariyanna, B" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="1 - 317" refId="B73" refString="Kariyanna, B, Mohan, M, Gupta, R, Vitali, F, 2017. The checklist of longhorn beetles (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae) from India. Zootaxa 4345 (1): 1 - 317, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4345.1.1" title="The checklist of longhorn beetles (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae) from India." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4345.1.1" volume="4345" year="2017">Kariyanna et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2457755512FA16EBFAA3947376D781E1" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="macau records">
<paragraph id="C3528E9747D78A5E4198C2195CA67549" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Macau records.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="11AA5C6D2E205DA3F46A5FD095E461EF" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Coloane Village, 1 Jun 2020, on mosquito trap in ablution block, R Perissinotto &amp; L Clennell (IZCAS); ibidem 2 May 2021, Lynette Clennell (https://www.inaturalist.org/observations/76790081).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E2CBFE22A99A7353D29B2E64F5FF57C7" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="C7BF974373D0A90BFA36B221DEBE0962" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="718631F4A5884AC42E938017E8FC4E7B" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
The only two specimens observed in Macau exhibited a total length of 9-9.5 mm and a maximum width of 4 mm. Its general morphology matches rather well that of 
<taxonomicName id="5A1490AEBDB551AD7B3E5FA2AE83553D" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pterolophia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pterolophia cervina" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cervina">
<emphasis id="8D1F7940FFAA3732EABB6622AC1F7FA8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Pterolophia cervina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gressit, 1939 from Guangdong, which was recently considered as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="C737D336FDB8E762FFD4080CB3B7CED0" authority="Pascoe, 1865" authorityName="Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Praonetha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Praonetha consularis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="consularis">
<emphasis id="9ABA749F2290BB0182554654C02B9E37" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Praonetha consularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Pascoe, 1866 (
<bibRefCitation id="15D528C446CCEEAE474CFCA9F3C827CB" author="Weigel, A" journalOrPublisher="Formosa Ecological Company, Taiwan" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B155" refString="Weigel, A, Meng, L-Z, Lin, M-Y, 2013. Contribution to the Fauna of Longhorn Beetles in the Naban River Watershed National Nature Reserve. Formosa Ecological Company, Taiwan" title="Contribution to the Fauna of Longhorn Beetles in the Naban River Watershed National Nature Reserve." year="2013">Weigel et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
). It also resembles closely 
<taxonomicName id="4C32FA3CC6BFE9ABAD840E446D14DBC5" genus="P." lsidName="P. (Mimoron) brevegibbosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="brevegibbosa" subGenus="Mimoron">P. (Mimoron) brevegibbosa</taxonomicName>
Pic, 1926 from Lantau Island, Hong Kong (
<bibRefCitation id="985D52CE83973889DA860EBD1732B595" author="Hayashi, M" journalOrPublisher="The Entomological Review of Japan" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="71 - 74" publicationUrl="http://coleoptera.sakura.ne.jp/ERJ/ERJ37(1)1982.pdf" refId="B61" refString="Hayashi, M, 1982. On Some Cerambycidae from Hong Kong (Coleoptera). The Entomological Review of Japan 37 (1): 71 - 74, http://coleoptera.sakura.ne.jp/ERJ/ERJ37(1)1982.pdf" title="On Some Cerambycidae from Hong Kong (Coleoptera)." url="http://coleoptera.sakura.ne.jp/ERJ/ERJ37(1)1982.pdf" volume="37" year="1982">Hayashi 1982</bibRefCitation>
, pl. 2, fig. 6). So, it is possible that all of them actually represent the same species, with the name 
<taxonomicName id="95047E2BCACE70E0C238AF296C751886" genus="P." lsidName="P. (P.) consularis" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="consularis" subGenus="P.">P. (P.) consularis</taxonomicName>
being the most senior. However, if the type species from Malaysia is different, then 
<taxonomicName id="558675C226120F432CE3F367FFB5A367" genus="P." lsidName="P. (M.) brevegibbosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="brevegibbosa" subGenus="M.">P. (M.) brevegibbosa</taxonomicName>
will be the senior name for the species from Macau, Guangdong, Hong Kong and Hainan Island. 
<bibRefCitation id="8028ED3AB655BFFAA78B6D5338AC8A53" author="Yiu, V" journalOrPublisher="Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B161" refString="Yiu, V, 2009. Longhorn Beetles of Hong Kong. Insect Fauna of Hong Kong, Fascicle 1. Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" title="Longhorn Beetles of Hong Kong. Insect Fauna of Hong Kong, Fascicle 1." year="2009">Yiu (2009)</bibRefCitation>
reported that larvae of this species in Hong Kong bore into plants of 
<taxonomicName id="817D7046B6A6757F45F6C46E6D0576A7" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Zea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Zea mays" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="mays">
<emphasis id="0C9461AC4013E3D8E3EFB5920EA73ECC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Zea mays</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="61DA29279AC5BA8229DAA14E4BA227E5" author="Hua, L-Z" journalOrPublisher="List of Chinese Insects" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="1 - 612" refId="B68" refString="Hua, L-Z, 2002. List of Chinese Insects. Zhongshan (Sun Yat-Sen) University Press, Guangzhou. List of Chinese Insects 2: 1 - 612" title="List of Chinese Insects. Zhongshan (Sun Yat-Sen) University Press, Guangzhou." volume="2" year="2002">Hua (2002)</bibRefCitation>
listed as host plant also 
<taxonomicName id="B7443E7DADD11F3DB018876CA6CF37DD" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Casuarinaceae" genus="Casuarina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Casuarina equisetifolia" order="Casuarinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="equisetifolia">
<emphasis id="3B03A830F12284753DBBA9AE347D6C32" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Casuarina equisetifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
